The paper deals with a communication problem in the presence of an adversarial jammer, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of an arbitrarily varying channel also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the concept of a myopic adversary may be relevant to security and privacy (cs.SI).
